'''Renato Salvatori''' ([[March 20]], [[1934]] - [[March 27]] [[1988]]) was a prolific [[Italy|Italian]] multi-purpose [[character actor]].

==Biography==
Salvatori was born in [[Seravezza]], [[province of Lucca]].

He started off handsomely as a romantic juvenile actor but after working with the powerful likes of directors [[Luchino Visconti]], [[Roberto Rossellini]] and [[Vittorio De Sica]] in the [[1960s]], turned into one of Italy's strongest characters actors of grim, harrowing [[drama]].

He met [[French people|French]] actress [[Annie Girardot]] on the set of the [[1960]] [[movie]] ''[[Rocco and His Brothers]]'' and married her on [[January 6]], [[1962]]. In sharp contrast to their off-camera relationship, in the movie Salvatori played a boxer-turned-thug who viciously rapes Annie, who played a prostitute. They had a daughter, Giulia; later they separated but never divorced.

Salvatori died in [[Rome]] of [[cirrhosis of the liver]]. 

